<br>
In the past, much posting here was simply raging at the &quot;opposition&quot;. Fun, and there is certainly a place for it on the  board,  but it doesn't pay the bills.<br>
<br>
The old mayor of Chicago, Dick Daley senior, remarked during the &quot;Troubles&quot; at the 1968 convention about the protesters:<br>
&quot;What trees do they plant?&quot;. As misguided as he may have been about what happened on the streets, his point is well taken. Other than griping, what do we CREATE?<br>
<br>
I see the Artemis Society's site as a great model for making something happen.<br>
  <br>
This board has potential if YOU get on board. Here is an example of what we can be doing:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.asi.org/">www.asi.org/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
They are CREATING a plan.<br>
<br>
yale<br>
