<br>
More back to the subject, inviting people in on discussions could be fun, so long as it's pretty controlled. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nebobgrenville>nebobgrenville</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://my.oregonstate.edu/courses/1/NE_114_X001_F2002/uploads/homepage/_1060577_1/triga.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 337<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(6/10/03 4:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=909.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Challenge to NS</span><hr size=1> Actualy a cross board discussion could be very interesting, we just have to make sure it remains a thoughtful discussion.<br>
<br>
